commit 32a161f5af8a77d4684da074d3dce9f0e94c5c6d
Author: Jarred Sumner <jarred@jarredsumner.com>
Date:   Tue May 19 22:16:03 2026 -0700

    bundler: close the main-thread perf gap vs Zig 1.3.14 (#31115)
    
    The Rust port was 1.10× slower than Zig 1.3.14 on the rolldown-benchmark
    `apps/10000` (and a 111k-file variant), with main-thread CPU ~22% higher
    despite ~29% less total CPU. The wall-clock gap was entirely main-thread
    serialization during the parse-result loop and link phase.
    
    ### Results (linux x64, 64-core)
    
    | | 100k wall | 100k main-thread | 10k wall | total CPU vs 1.3.14 |
    |---|---|---|---|---|
    | `main` HEAD | 3819 ms | 3065 ms | 470 ms | −29% |
    | **this branch** | **3443 ms** | **~2680 ms** | **429 ms** | **−41%** |
    | `bun-1.3.14` | 3398 ms | 2417 ms | 422 ms | — |
    
    vs current canary: **1.05× faster** on 10k.
    
    ### What changed
    
    **Arena-allocate everything `deinit_without_freeing_arena` was
    iterating** — Zig bulk-freed `graph.heap`; the port had ~18 per-module
    column drop loops walking
    `Part`/`JSMeta`/`InputFile`/`LinkerGraph::File` global-heap fields.
    Routed `DependencyList`, `PartSymbolUseMap`, `TopLevelSymbolToParts`,
    `RefImportData`, `ResolvedExports`, `quoted_source_contents`,
    `line_offset_table`, etc. through `AstAlloc` so the slab-only
    `MultiArrayList` drop strands nothing. `ArrayHashMap.index` now uses
    `HashTable<u32, IndexAlloc<A>>` so its bucket array follows the map's
    allocator. The teardown function is now ~3 lines (css + free_list).
    
    **Drop the 48 spurious `#[cold]` on `bundle_v2.rs`** — the port marked
    every public method cold (Zig had zero); they pessimized the main-thread
    parse/link hot path.
    
    **Resolver: stop copying `MatchResult` (~300B) by value through 7
    levels** — converted `load_node_modules` / `load_as_file_or_directory` /
    `handle_esm_resolution` / `resolve_without_remapping` /
    `match_tsconfig_paths` and friends to take `out: &mut MatchResult` and
    return a small `MatchStatus` enum. `load_node_modules` self-time dropped
    from 1.28% to <0.26%.
    
    **`Path::name` is computed on demand** — `PathName` (4×16B substrings of
    `text`) was stored inline, making `Path` 120 bytes. Now `fn name() ->
    PathName` parses `text`; `Path` is 56 bytes (const-asserted).
    
    **Tree-shaking / code-splitting**:
    - Dropped per-part `Vec` clones in `mark_{file,part}_live` and
    `scanImportsAndExports` step-5 (~1.1M alloc+free pairs); iterate by
    index and re-borrow per iteration.
    - Packed the 5 fat-slice params of the recursive functions into
    `TreeShakeCtx`/`CodeSplitCtx` so calls fit in registers.
    - Moved `Part::is_live` to a per-file `AutoBitSet` so `mark_part_live`
    checks the bit before loading the 272-byte `Part`.
    
    **Hashers**: `BSSMapInner::IndexMap` was `std::HashMap<u64,_>` with
    default `RandomState` — wyhash then SipHash on every dir-cache probe.
    Now identity. `ArrayHashMap`'s `AutoContext` switched from wyhash to
    `FxHasher` for `Ref`/int keys.
    
    **`dir_info_cached_maybe_log`**: outlined the cache-miss tail; the hot
    function's stack frame is now 72 bytes (was ~8.6KB with stack probes).
    `DirInfo::get_parent` inlines now that `hash_map_instance`'s lazy-init
    is `#[cold]`.
    
    ### Not done
    
    - The remaining ~250ms main-thread gap on 100k is spread across
    `scan_imports_and_exports` self-time, `match_import_with_export`,
    `FindImportedPartsVisitor::visit`, and `on_parse_task_complete`/barrel —
    each <2% and largely cache-miss-bound on per-file arena data accessed in
    graph order.
    - Per-`node_modules`-`DirInfo` package-result cache was prototyped then
    dropped (caching in-memory ops is the wrong fix; the ops were made cheap
    instead). Neither esbuild nor Zig 1.3.14 has one.
    
    ---------
    
    Co-authored-by: autofix-ci[bot] <114827586+autofix-ci[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>

