commit 85534281c6de07fc0376ad1af0bc60f3fd7dfa05
Author: Jarred Sumner <jarred@jarredsumner.com>
Date:   Thu Jun 4 20:30:22 2026 -0700

    Resolve the audited TODO(port)/TODO(b2)/PORT NOTE backlog (#31783)
    
    # Resolve the audited TODO(port)/TODO(b2)/PORT NOTE backlog
    
    ## What this PR does
    
    The Rust port accumulated a large backlog of `TODO(port)` / `TODO(b2-*)`
    markers and
    "PORT NOTE" comments — a mix of stale organizational notes,
    completed-but-unverified
    debts, real small bugs, and genuinely hard lifetime/GC restructures.
    This PR drains
    that backlog: every one of the 2,327 audited markers (plus 1,342 PORT
    NOTE comment
    lines across 346 files) was individually resolved — fixed,
    verified-and-documented,
    deleted as stale, or split into a tracked follow-up work order.
    
    Net diff: 1,025 files, +13,985 / −14,705.
    
    ## Method
    
    Audit-driven, per-file passes: each group of files got a fix pass, two
    independent
    adversarial reviews, and a repair pass addressing reviewer findings; a
    second phase
    drained cross-file escalations and leftover markers the same way.
    
    ## Summary of actions
    
    | Action | Count |
    |---|---|
    | Stale/organizational TODO removed (content verified first) | ~1,240 |
    | Load-bearing comment kept, untagged to plain/SAFETY/PERF comment |
    ~780 tagged comments + 1,342 PORT NOTE lines |
    | Real code fix or completed verification debt | ~495 |
    | Pure bookkeeping comment lines deleted | ~280 |
    | Split into a tracked follow-up work order (marker kept) | 101 markers
    → 43 work-order files |
    | Marker described already-landed work | 18 |
    | Covered by an open PR; left alone | 6 |
    | Fix reverted after review (then redone correctly later) | 1 |
    
    ## Notable code fixes by subsystem
    
    - **install**: lockfile migration cursor pointers replaced with safe
    pushes; SaveTask
    no longer borrows registry Scope across the threadpool; pre-hashed maps
    switched to
    identity hashing; detached-parent lifecycle-script completion uses the
    atomic
      increment the Zig source specified; dead ScriptRunEnvironment removed.
    - **jsc bindings**: restored dropped debug asserts (JSCell getter-setter
    types, WTF-8
    printer validation); `Strong::get` reads the handle slot like the Zig
    original;
    member-binding tracking wired into JSCell accessors; hot-reload error
    traces wired.
    - **runtime**: `test.each` arguments are now GC-rooted for the duration
    of label
    formatting/binding; html_rewriter end-tag callbacks use RAII protection;
    missing
    `globalThis.wasmSourceBytes` wiring for compiled-wasm entrypoints;
    server request
    error logging prints the JS stack trace; stream byte-blob fast path uses
    an
      uninitialized-then-copied Uint8Array like upstream.
    - **cli**: `bun init` full-stack template runs `bun install` with stdin
    ignored
    (matching upstream behavior) via a new no-stdin spawn helper with
    per-platform
    handling; `open_url` actually spawns the opener; missing-entrypoint
    fallback to help
    restored; completions install command delegates to the full
    implementation.
    - **js_printer / js_parser / ast**: template-literal folding is written
    back so
    minified output uses it; identifier-range lookup is a faithful
    full-Unicode port;
    per-call heap allocation removed from the printer's fmt path; macro
    enablement
      matches the wasm gate.
    - **css**: border-image fallbacks moved instead of deep-cloned; font
    handler uses
      single-lookup map entries.
    - **bundler/resolver/sourcemap**: entry-point offset for server
    components restored;
    renamer teardown matches upstream defer; several `'static` lifetime
    erasures replaced
      with real borrows or owned copies.
    - **crash handler / analytics**: feature counters (todo_panic,
    unsupported_uv_function)
      and telemetry-enabled checks now match the spec.
    - **collections**: release-mode panic on >256-byte keys in the comptime
    string map
    fixed with a heap fallback; dead APIs removed; Zig-PRNG-faithful tests
    ported.
    - **windows**: Win32 error codes map through a real errno-name hook
    instead of
    collapsing to "Unexpected"; long-path error split (FileNotFound vs
    NameTooLong).
    - Plus a long tail of dead-code deletion, error-type narrowing, and
      verification-debt closure — full per-entry list in the group reports.
    
    ## What deliberately remains
    
    101 `TODO(...)` markers remain in-tree, each claimed by a written work
    order.
    These are the changes that should not land blind in a bulk branch: GC
    rooting of bare
    JSValue fields, crate-wide arena-lifetime threading in bun_css,
    cross-thread
    ownership restructures (installer task queue, copy_file, dns caching
    backrefs),
    Stacked-Borrows provenance hardening, Windows fd-ownership modeling, and
    a ~1,400-line
    diff test-suite port. Each gets a dedicated, individually reviewable
    follow-up PR.
    
    Zero "PORT NOTE" strings remain. A follow-up sweep on this branch also
    removes all
    remaining Zig references from comments (~18k lines: file/line
    cross-references,
    std.* stdlib mentions, quoted Zig syntax, divergence notes) — this
    codebase is a
    standalone Rust implementation and its comments now read that way.
    SAFETY
    justifications were rewritten in terms of the Rust code's own invariants
    rather
    than deleted. References to current identifiers (ZigString etc.) are
    unchanged.
    
    ## Verification
    
    - Full debug build (linux-x64, ASAN) compiles and links clean. Three
    issues were
    caught and fixed by the compile pass: a unit-struct FFI-alignment marker
    in
    `uws_sys` rewritten to the zero-length-array idiom, missing parens in
    two
    `debug_assert!`s, and a `CompileResultSlots::get_mut` accessor added so
    the
      DevServer HTML ownership transfer borrows mutably without new unsafe.
    - Smoke-tested: eval, timers, `Bun.$` shell, `bun test`. The
    `setTimeout` suite's
      3 leak-threshold failures reproduce identically on main's debug build
      (pre-existing, not from this branch).
    - Cross-target `cargo check` (windows/macos/linux × x64/aarch64) run
    before push.
    - Two CI failures found and fixed on this branch:
    `parsePackedFeaturesList()`
    updated for the reshaped `define_features!` macro, and a hot-reload
    server
    registration bug — `NewServer::init` moves the config into the server,
    so the
      hot-map insert after init read an empty id and panicked on the second
    `Bun.serve` under `--hot`. The path was unreachable before this branch's
    `hot_map()` lazy-init fix exposed it; registration now reads the
    server's own
      config, and `HTTPServerAgent.test.ts` passes.
    
    Caveats worth knowing during review: a handful of fixes are in
    `#[cfg(windows)]` /
    wasm32 arms that only the cross-target check pass exercises, and the
    GC-adjacent
    changes (test.each rooting, html_rewriter protection, Strong::get)
    deserve close
    reading — pointers to the riskiest items are in the campaign's synthesis
    notes.
    
